      "note": "~$850M/day midpoint Day 61 ceasefire-phase ($600M-$1,100M range; CSIS Cancian/Park) \u2014 Pentagon issued no Apr 29 daily figure; with ceasefire holding for Day 21 and no new strikes, daily run-rate remains in steady-state range. \u26a0\ufe0f HASC HEARING APR 29 (Hegseth/Caine/Hurst, first since war began): Acting Comptroller Jules Hurst pegged CUMULATIVE Operation Epic Fury cost at ~$25 BILLION (mostly munitions); Hegseth said any Iran-specific supplemental will be 'less than $25B' \u2014 averaged across 61 days that implies ~$410M/day, half this dashboard's modeled rate. Hurst's $25B figure is sharply lower than dashboard's ~$51.85B midpoint \u2014 Rep. Khanna challenged figure as omitting replacement weapons, equipment damage, and broader consumer hit ('totally off\u2026 incompetence'). Hegseth listed 14 critical munitions for replenishment (Patriot, THAAD, SM-3, SM-6, AMRAAM, JASSM, PrSM); FY2027 Pentagon budget request $1.5T. BLOCKADE DAY 17 \u2014 3 U.S. CARRIERS in CENTCOM (Lincoln, Ford, Bush; first time since OIF 2003), 31st MEU active (boarded M/V Blue Star III Apr 28; cumulative redirects 39).",
